column17: The incident occurred 400 kilometers north of Cotonou
column18: 03/15/2007: Gunmen fired on a convoy carrying the president of Benin, Yaha Boni, who emerged unharmed but four guards were wounded. The attack occurred when Boni was returning from a meeting, 400 kilometers (250 miles) north of the main city, Cotonou.  No claim of responsibility was reported.
column97: Kalashnikovs and other automatic weapons were used
